  "HCl (hydrochloric acid) and KOH (potassium hydroxide)": "",
  "HNO3 (nitric acid) and KOH (potassium hydroxide)": "",
  "H2SO4 (sulfuric acid) and NaOH (sodium hydroxide)": "",
  "H3PO4 (phosphoric acid) and LiOH (lithium hydroxide)": "",
  "KNO3 contains K+ (from KOH) and NO3- (from HNO3). So the parent acid is nitric acid (HNO3) and the parent base is potassium hydroxide (KOH).": "",
  "In a lab, a student neutralizes phosphoric acid with sodium hydroxide and needs to name the resulting salt. The correct name is:": "",
  "Sodium chloride because chloride comes from the acid": "",
  "Sodium phosphate because phosphate comes from the acid": "",
  "Sodium sulfate because sulfate comes from the acid": "",
  "Sodium nitrate because nitrate comes from the acid": "",
  "Phosphoric acid (H3PO4) provides the phosphate ion (PO4 3-), and NaOH provides Na+. The salt is sodium phosphate (Na3PO4).": "",
  "A student dissolves the salt NaCl in water and tests the pH. The pH is approximately 7. This makes sense because NaCl is formed from:": "",
  "A weak acid and a strong base producing a basic salt": "",
  "A strong acid and a weak base producing an acidic salt": "",
  "A strong acid and a strong base producing a neutral salt": "",
  "A weak acid and a weak base producing an unknown salt": "",
  "NaCl comes from HCl (strong acid) and NaOH (strong base). Salts from strong acid + strong base are neutral in solution (pH approximately 7).": "",
  "A student needs to write the formula for the salt produced when sulfuric acid reacts with aluminum hydroxide. The correct salt formula is:": "",
  "Al(SO4)3 because aluminum has a charge of positive three": "",
  "AlSO4 because one aluminum pairs with one sulfate ion": "",
  "Al2(SO4)3 because charges must balance between the ions": "",
  "Al3SO4 because three aluminum ions pair with one sulfate": "",
  "Al3+ and SO4 2- must balance charges: 2 Al3+ (+6) and 3 SO4 2- (-6) gives Al2(SO4)3 (aluminum sulfate).": "",
  "A chemist identifies a white crystalline salt and determines it contains barium and nitrate ions. The salt most likely formed from the neutralization of:": "",
  "Hydrochloric acid and barium hydroxide in a lab reaction": "",
