  "A strong acid and a weak base making an acidic salt": "",
  "Two strong acids reacting with each other in solution": "",
  "Sodium acetate is from acetic acid (weak acid) and NaOH (strong base). The acetate ion hydrolyzes in water, making the solution slightly basic (pH > 7).": "",
